<type_def lang="typescript" ?>
export interface ApplyPatchOuterInput { patchText?: string; patch?: string; }
export type ApplyPatchOuterOutput = string;
export type apply_patch = (input: ApplyPatchOuterInput) => ApplyPatchOuterOutput;
</?>

<warning ?>
Use this tool for structured patch-first text edits.
</?>

<warning ?>
Prefer small hunks and named anchors such as `@@ def foo` or `@@ class Bar` when the target file has repeated blocks.
</?>

<warning ?>
Patch envelope:
- Start with `*** Begin Patch`
- End with `*** End Patch`
- Use `*** Add File`, `*** Update File`, `*** Delete File`, and `*** Move to` as needed.
</?>

<warning ?>
For update hunks, each hunk should begin with one or more `@@ ...` anchor lines followed by `+`, `-`, and space-prefixed lines.
</?>

<warning ?>
If a patch fails, reread the target file and rebuild a smaller patch from fresh context instead of retrying the same stale hunk.
</?>

<warning ?>
Do not use shell-simulated editing for normal text changes when ApplyPatch can express the edit directly.
</?>
